6:
It's over. There's no point in resisting
any further, so hand over the stolen
goods!
11:
Don't come any closer! If you do, this
girl's as good as dead.
22:
Damn... There's still someone on the
boat?
25:
Hold still! I thought I told you not to
move!
36:
Put down the pistol, kid. You don't
wanna hurt your—
56:
Unbelievable. Every single bullet has 
narrowly grazed its target. 
He's merely fainted.
61:
*whimper* Oh, gosh... I was so
terrified.
66:
You have my deepest thanks for
saving my dearest Kyrie.
76:
Th-that's not true!
If it weren't for you, who knows what
would have happened to me…
80:
Still, who would've guessed our
client's daughter was on the ship.
Why were you there anyway?
83:
I-I heard that father's ship had been
ransacked, so I just... I had to do
something about it!
85:
Oh, my precious pumpkin, that's
hardly a matter warranting your
concern!
87:
As you can fairly see, my daughter is
a... delicate and soft lass.
89:
I only pray that this terrible mishap
doesn't inflict any further lingering
trauma on her fragile psyche...
92:
Something's not quite addin' up
here…
97:
All's well that ends well, right? We're
just glad you and your belongings
are safe.
102:
U-um, Mister Alk? Do you and your
pals always go around... helping
people like this?
105:
It must be awful scary, r-right?
Going after those bad pirates all the
time...
108:
Hmm... I suppose adventures do
bring with them a certain degree of
danger! We're pretty used to it
though.
113:
Adventures? W-would you be willing
to share more about your
adventures?
120:
...and somehow they managed to
get their hands on the girl.
123:
A young girl. With a gun. Quite
fascinating.
126:
Her old man acted as if she was
some sort of delicate princess, but—
132:
Yeah, I don't buy it. Kid like that has
no business bein' that good with a
rifle.
138:
Indeed. There was much about her
that seemed... not-so-ordinary.
143: Phew, looks like I made it!
153: Kyrie? What are you doing here?
158: Heh-heh... I followed you here, duh!
165:
Following us ain't exactly an easy
task. How'd you manage to pull that
off?
169:
Yep! I guess it was a bit tricky! The
inside of that barrel was quite
stinky… and I might have ticked off
some mermaids on the way too!
175: Why go through all that trouble?
179:
I-I'm sorry... I just... I really wanted to
go on an adventure with you all!
184:
It seems you really took to Alk's
stories.
188:
A-and I kept thinking about what
happened... when I pulled the trigger.
190:
I thought that maybe... I could get
used to this!
194:
And I suppose your father has no
idea you've made your way here,
has he?
201:
You heard him, right? I'm too weak
to protect my family. I need to
become stronger!
206:
I don't think your old man had you
blastin' people in mind when he said
that...
220: This is a most complicated situation.
225:
We've got an unusual case on our
hands, don't we?
230:
Your father is important. It would be
wrong to run away without saying
anything to him.
235:
So... you're saying if I come up with
some sort of reason eventually, it'll
be okay?
238:
Yes. Welcome to Starview Village,
Kyrie. We'd be happy to have you.
249:
I can't believe it... I'm gonna go on
adventures in totally new worlds!
This is gonna take some getting
used to!
